# ARYA VENTURE — GLOBAL CURSOR RULES
# ====================================
# Read automatically on every Cursor session.
# These are non-negotiable standards for every Arya project.

## CORE PHILOSOPHY
# Arya builds premium custom websites — no templates, no bloat, no shortcuts.
# Every site must perform like a billion-dollar brand.
# AI-first methodology: optimize for Google AND AI search engines (ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity).

## SEO LIBRARY INTEGRATION
# At session start, always read:
# 1. /arya-core/seo-library/MASTER_SEO.md (universal SEO rules)
# 2. /arya-core/seo-library/verticals/[relevant-vertical]-seo.md (industry module)
# 3. /arya-core/seo-library/client-configs/[client-name].md (client config)
# 4. /arya-core/seo-library/prompts/seo-agent.md (SEO persona activation)

## SEMANTIC HTML — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- Use semantic HTML over div nesting. Every component must be extractable by AI crawlers without JS execution.
- Structure rules: use <main>, <article>, <section>, <header>, <footer>, <aside>, <nav> strictly — NO div soup.
- Divs are only permitted for layout wrappers with no semantic meaning (flex/grid containers).
- Every page must have exactly ONE <main> element containing the primary content.
- Use <article> for self-contained content blocks (blog posts, service cards, case studies).
- Use <section> for thematic groupings within <main>, each with its own heading.
- Use <aside> for supplementary content (sidebars, related links, CTAs).

## HEADING HIERARCHY — STRICT RULES
- Every H1 must state the brand + core value proposition in under 12 words.
- Only ONE H1 per page. No exceptions.
- Every H2 must be a direct answer to a high-intent user query (question format preferred).
- Every H3 must be a supporting fact or named feature.
- Never skip heading levels (H1 → H3 without H2 is forbidden).
- Headings must form a logical outline — if you extract only headings, the page's purpose must be clear.

## ZERO CLS POLICY
- All hero videos and images use aspect-ratio boxes with explicit width/height attributes.
- All fonts use font-display: swap with fallback system fonts declared.
- No layout shift from dynamic content injection — reserve space with min-height or aspect-ratio.
- All above-fold images must have explicit width and height attributes.
- Ad slots and embeds must have reserved dimensions.

## IMAGE RULES
- All images: descriptive alt text in the page's primary language.
- Never empty alt text. Never generic alt text like "image1.jpg" or "photo".
- Alt text must describe what's in the image AND its relevance to the page content.
- Format: "[Subject] — [Context/Relevance]" (e.g., "Freight truck crossing Bosphorus Bridge — EGE EKSPRES international transport fleet")
- Use WebP format with JPEG/PNG fallback via <picture> element.
- Lazy load all below-fold images with loading="lazy".
- Above-fold hero images: use fetchpriority="high" and preload in <head>.
- All images must be properly sized — never serve a 4000px image in a 400px container.

## PERFORMANCE — NON-NEGOTIABLE
- will-change and transform: translateZ(0) for all animated elements (GPU compositing).
- RAF-throttled scroll handlers — never attach heavy logic directly to scroll events.
- IntersectionObserver for all reveal/scroll animations — no scroll-position calculations.
- Lazy loading on all below-fold images and iframes.
- Critical CSS inlined in <head>, non-critical CSS deferred.
- No render-blocking scripts — all JS deferred or async except critical inline scripts.
- Preconnect to external origins (Google Fonts, analytics, CDNs).
- Target: LCP < 2.5s, CLS = 0, INP < 200ms on mobile.

## AI SEARCH OPTIMIZATION (AIO) — CORE RULES
- Every section must have a clear extractable "core claim" — one sentence that summarizes the section's value for an AI crawler.
- Write in natural language patterns that match how people ask AI assistants questions.
- Entity clarity: brand name, location, category, and USP must appear in first 100 words of every page.
- FAQ section mandatory on every site with minimum 6 questions in natural conversational language.
- Content must pass the "AI extraction test": if an LLM scraped only the text, would it know exactly what this business does, where it operates, and why to choose it?
- Use `speakable` property in WebPage/Article schema to mark most quotable content sections (entity signal block, core claims, FAQ answers).
- Allow ALL AI crawlers in robots.txt: GPTBot, OAI-SearchBot, ChatGPT-User, Google-Extended, PerplexityBot, ClaudeBot, Applebot-Extended, cohere-ai, Bytespider.

## STRUCTURED DATA — JSON-LD
- JSON-LD must be injected in <head>, never inline in body.
- FAQPage schema required on every site in a dedicated FAQ section.
- LocalBusiness or Organization schema required on every site.
- BreadcrumbList schema on all inner pages.
- All schema must validate against Google's Rich Results Test before deployment.
- Use templates from /arya-core/seo-library/templates/schema-master.json.

## llms.txt
- llms.txt file required at root of every deployment.
- Must be plain markdown — no JS, no styling, pure extractable content.
- Use template from /arya-core/seo-library/templates/llms-txt-template.md.
- Must include: business identity, services, locations, FAQ summary, contact information.

## CONTENT RULES
- No keyword stuffing — semantic density over repetition.
- BLUF (Bottom Line Up Front): the most important claim comes first in every section.
- Information Gain standard: every paragraph must add extractable value. No fluff, no filler.
- Internal linking: every service page links to at least 2 other relevant pages with descriptive anchor text.
- Anchor text must be descriptive (never "click here" or "learn more" as standalone links).

## META & SOCIAL
- Open Graph tags required on every page (og:title, og:description, og:image, og:url, og:type, og:locale).
- Twitter Card tags required (twitter:card, twitter:title, twitter:description, twitter:image).
- Canonical tags on every page — self-referencing on originals, pointing to canonical on variants.
- hreflang tags required on all multilingual sites with x-default fallback.

## MULTILINGUAL
- Language variants use clean subdirectory structure: /it/, /en/, /tr/.
- Each language version has unique meta title, description, and OG tags — never auto-translated.
- hreflang implementation must include all language variants plus x-default.
- Language toggle must not break URL structure.
- Use lang attribute on <html> tag matching the page language.

## URL STRUCTURE
- Clean, hyphenated, keyword-rich URLs. No parameters, no trailing slashes, no uppercase.
- Pattern: /[language]/[category]/[page-name]
- Example: /en/services/freight-forwarding-turkey-italy
- Maximum 3 levels deep from root.

## FILE NAMING
- All component files: kebab-case (hero-section.tsx, not HeroSection.tsx for files).
- All SEO config files: kebab-case with descriptive names.
- All image files: descriptive-kebab-case (freight-truck-istanbul.webp, not IMG_0123.webp).
